title: Weird behaviour of binary_search for &str vectors and string vectors
body:
I tried this code: ```rust #![allow(unused)] fn main() { let k="Ring"; let s:Vec<&str>= vec!["Hello","Welcome","Ring"]; assert_eq!(s.binary_search(&k),Ok(2)); } fn main(){ let b=String::from("Calm"); let a:Vec=vec![String::from("Ritchie"),String::from("Hello"),String::from("Calm")]; assert_eq!(a.binary_search(&b),Ok(2)); } ``` I expected to see this happen: *explanation* I expected left to be equal to right Instead, this happened: *explanation* Instead left was Err(1) and right Ok(2). For string left was Err(0) and right Ok(2). ### Meta Bug also exists on nightly and beta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0 (a55dd71d5 2022-09-19) binary: rustc commit-hash: a55dd71d5fb0ec5a6a3a9e8c27b2127ba491ce52 commit-date: 2022-09-19 host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc release: 1.64.0 LLVM version: 14.0.6 ```
